<h1><%= @domain.base_domain %> instructions</h1>
<p>In order to get your Derpback plugin to render on a page, you need to do three things:</p>
<h2>1) Include jQuery</h2>
<p>If you haven't already, you need to include jQuery in your page. The quickest way to do accomplish this is by adding a line like this: <pre class="prettyprint linenums">SCRIPT SRC='' /SCRIPT</pre> </p> 
<h2>2) Include Javascript file</h2>
<p> Download our script file. Upload it somewhere on your server.  &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<%= link_to "Download", download_path(@domain), class: 'btn btn-primary' %> </p>
<p style="color:red">Do not use this script on other domains, or feedback will not be reported correctly. Scripts are custom, so get a new one for each domain from its instructions page.</p>
<h2>3) Initialise the feedback plugin</h2> <p>Put this code after your <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> tag and <strong>replace the bold part with the path to the javascript file you downloaded in step 2.</strong></p>
<pre class="prettyprint linenums">&lt;script type=&quot;text/javascript&quot; src=&quot<strong>/jquery.derpback.<%=@domain.base_domain%>.js</strong>&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;feedback-div&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;script&gt;
  $(&quot;#feedback-div&quot;).feedback()
&lt;/script&gt;
</pre>
<p>Done! Load the page add you should see a badge like the one on the right hand side of this page.</p>
<p>When people fill in the feedback form, the feedback will appear on this site, as well as send an email to <%=@domain.user.email%>.</p>
